<div id="review_2878777056" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2878777056" />
    <a title="Snigdha" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22247463-snigdha"><img alt="Snigdha" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1539528012p2/22247463.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2878777056?book_show_action=true">Jul 14, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Snigdha" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Snigdha" href="/user/show/22247463-snigdha">Snigdha</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780451226815" href="/book/show/6001011-rooftops-of-tehran">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22247463-snigdha?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22247463-snigdha?shelf=romance">romance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2878777056" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10507070500832709782"><b>“Loving is a laborious and complex business.” : 2.4/5 </b><br/><br/>I picked up this book thinking it will be the same as all those books set in middle eastern backdrop, and it will be more focused upon the culture and their people but it is a plain, humdrum love story which has nothing great to offer from a reader&apos;s perspective. <br/><br/>This book is set in 1970&apos;s Iran, where a teenage guy falls in love with his mentor&apos;s girlfriend, who is elder to him as well, at first he tries to ward off his feelings for her but w</span>
  <span id="freeText10507070500832709782" style="display:none"><b>“Loving is a laborious and complex business.” : 2.4/5 </b><br /><br />I picked up this book thinking it will be the same as all those books set in middle eastern backdrop, and it will be more focused upon the culture and their people but it is a plain, humdrum love story which has nothing great to offer from a reader's perspective. <br /><br />This book is set in 1970's Iran, where a teenage guy falls in love with his mentor's girlfriend, who is elder to him as well, at first he tries to ward off his feelings for her but with the turn of events he finds himself helplessly falling for her and be love lorn till the climax of the book.<br /><br />The writing is very much plain, agreed and basic, many of the places you feel Deja vu like you have read and heard these lines a million times before, also many lines are repetitive in the book. The plot is very predictable and expected, there is only one high point in the whole book, but soon you guess what will happen next. Author could have included many romantic verses and interesting character build up, but he choose to write a mundane story which seemed to be told for millionth time. <br /><br />Overall it's a very average romance novel, which even left unread will cause no pain.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10507070500832709782" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

